title: DAY-Shift Report 1/17/2021 Mon
text: PROGRAM: SPEAR to BEAMS delivering 500mA to users with top-off every 5 mins. BEAMLINES: All open except BLs 4, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, 12, 15, 17 (BLs with LN monos). 1024 All open, except BL17. 1010 When opening BL7, MM1 does not register as open. Closed and re-opened stoppers four times, open status achieved. FAULTS: None. EXPERIMENTS: 1220 BL7-3 user support. LytleFocus motor had stopped responding to move commands and was not showing current position. Same with all other motors. Followed ops manual protocol to stop and restart ICS data collection software. This did not resolve problem. Found WebXAS help webpage, from there restarted DAQS and XASUTILS servers, motor communication restored. User back online at 1250. OPERATIONS: 0700 No LN delivery overnight, another call to Airgas suggests delivery expected 9-11am. 0845 Forced filled BL 15 and 17 messers, both from 40ish percent up to 75 percent. 1000 LN delivery to Tank 5B from 48 to 128 inches. 1000-1024 Restored messer pump frequencies and opened all beamlines. 1040 Filled RHS dewar at LN fill station. 1355 Filled LHS dewar at LN fill station. 1645 Called Airgas for update on next LN deliver (since we didnât get above 130â first alarm level). No deliveries planned, operator placed an order for LN which will be scheduled by tomorrow. Order number OZ0213811.

title: * Re: Not all contactor lights in LI30 were flashing - lights were flashing, but...
text: Staged operator on the BSY side of the 30-BSY wooden door and they observed lights flashing throughout LI30 during the two minute timeout. Once the timeout completed there was one bulb approximately 2 meters east of the manway alcove that was on steady bright (it flashed during two minute timeout, but remained on steady bright at the conclusion). At the conclusion of the two minute timeout, the rest of the bulbs in LI30 (excluding the lone bulb above) were completely off. When the state machine is in zone entry enabled, we expect the lights to be on steady dim when LI30 is time out in No Access. Also, one of the contactor lights at the manway is always on regardless of timeout status. All of this is CATERed. Discussed everything above with Paul Miller, and he was okay with us signing off that the lights flashed during the two minute timeout. The rest of the issues will be resolved during a PAMM.
